entries.femaleVariant: Whatcha got?
Tell me about the casino.
Sell anything that might pique my curiosity?
entries.maleVariant: You sell anything that might pique my curiosity?

entries.femaleVariant: Have a look.
How's the casino trade? Any big wins out there?
Of course. Anyone can win big. You just have to want it.
See a lot of Tygers. They run this place?
entries.maleVariant: I see a lot of Tygers. They run this place?

entries.femaleVariant: That's right – and very well. Know what else they do well? Break the knees of people who ask questions.
Woman used to work here, a netrunner. Name's Vortex – you know 'er?
I see you are searching for trouble. Whatever your reason, don't involve me. I know nothing.
Hey, how's the cashflow look?
Don't even ask. It's ennies. It's pathetic.
Say what you will about Vortex, she could work the machines. Not like our new gonk.
Talk. Or it's trouble you'll find.
I know you can help.
I'm not talking. Fuck off.
Trouble's what you'll find if you don't start talkin'.
Another word, I call security.
Lot of Tygers here.
What happened to Vortex?
Why not play yourself, then?
I dunno... It's against my religion... or whatever. I'm a Muslim.
Mhm. Yeah, see you also sell alcohol.
entries.maleVariant: Heh, yeah... See you also sell alcohol.

entries.femaleVariant: What, you a fuckin' expert on the Torah now? Mind your own business.
Have it your way.
Fine. Forget I even asked.
Thanks. You know... you're OK.
This Vortex you care so much for – she cheated them, OK? So they threw her body in the sewer.
You think that's got me spooked? I ain't scared of them. You shout a thing, I shoot the place up, starting with you.
entries.maleVariant: You think that's got me spooked? I ain't scared of 'em. You shout a thing, I shoot the place up, startin' with you.

entries.femaleVariant: Really think that'd put this all behind you? I still learn what I wanna know, somethin' happens your chooms don't like, then they remember who you talked to today. Whether you actually kept your mouth shut or not.
entries.maleVariant: You really think that'd put this all behind you? I still learn what I wanna know, somethin' happens your chooms don't like, then they remember who you talked to today. Whether you actually kept your mouth shut or not.

entries.femaleVariant: Must know somethin'. You're the barkeep, after all. Everyone's liquored lips start flappin' and you're the only pair of sober ears around.
Tell me what you know, I go about my biz quietly. No one finds out, no one comes knockin' for you.
entries.maleVariant: Tell me what I wanna know, and I go about my biz quietly. No one finds out, no one comes knockin' for ya.

entries.femaleVariant: Same spot the kitchen dumps used cooking oil. Bodies there don't last long. That's all I know, so fucking leave me alone.
